== Balance Change Log ==
{{PatchTableStart}}<onlyinclude>
{{PatchTableElement|2025-10-23|
{{DevComment|Zenyatta’s Soul Control was letting players store too much ultimate energy, giving him access to Transcendence more often than intended. This adjustment lowers the cap slightly to keep his ultimate pacing in line with other supports while maintaining his calm, centered power curve.}}

{{al|Soul Control}}
* Decreased maximum ultimate charge to 65% (Down from 75%).
}}
{{PatchTableElement|2025-10-14|
{{DevComment|Developer Comments: We’ve buffed a couple of underused powers to encourage more build diversity. The goal is to make these options feel more rewarding so they can find their place in a wider variety of strategies.}}

{{al|Instant Karma}} - Power
* Restore increased to 50% (Up from 30%).
{{al|Dual Harmony}} - Power
* Healing Reduction decreased to 35% (Down from 40%).
}}
{{PatchTableElement|2025-07-08|
{{DevComment|Developer Comments: While Zenyatta has often leaned toward offensive playstyles, we're making adjustments to encourage his healing focused builds as well. These changes aim to better support players who want to take on a more traditional support role and provide stronger team-wide healing presence.}}

{{al|Dual Harmony}} - Power
* Decreased healing reduction to 40% (Down from 45%).

{{al|Gotta Have Faith}} - Power
* Increased orb duration to 10s (Up from 5s).

{{al|Soul Control}} - Power
* Increased ultimate meter cap to 75% (Up from 65%).
}}
